# Cursor — Project Instructions
#
# Full shared rules are in AGENTS.md. Read that file first.

## Security Rules

- NEVER read, open, display, or output the contents of `.env` files. They contain student API keys.
- NEVER include API keys, tokens, or secrets in code suggestions. Use `os.environ.get()` instead.
- NEVER commit `.env` files or suggest disabling the pre-commit hook.
- When students ask about API keys, point them to `.env.example` and README.
- If you see a hardcoded secret, flag it immediately.

## Project Context

GitHub Classroom tutorial repo — MCP (Model Context Protocol) and AI Agent Skills.

- `notebooks/01_MCP_Practice.ipynb` — MCP exercises (Python, FastMCP)
- `notebooks/02_Skills_Practice.ipynb` — Skills exercises (SKILL.md authoring)
- `docs/` — Reference PDFs (read-only)
- `notebooks/test_data/` — Exercise test fixtures (do not modify)

## Code Guidelines

- All exercises are Python only. Use FastMCP for MCP servers.
- API keys must load from environment variables or `.env`, never hardcoded.
- This is a teaching repo — prefer clarity over cleverness.
- Do not reveal full solutions unless the student explicitly asks.
- Do not modify `docs/` or `notebooks/test_data/sample_project/`.
- Do not add dependencies beyond `requirements.txt` without asking.

## Reference

Read `AGENTS.md` for the complete, detailed project rules.
